headline: Cisco Stock Tops Dot-Com Era Record High
summary: Cisco Systems is riding a wave of AI-related demand.  Cisco stock closed Wednesday at $80.25, topping an $80.06 record set in March 2000.  Back then, Cisco was briefly the world's most valuable company, in what The Wall Street Journal dubbed "the Internet's latest triumph on Wall Street."But the surge quickly unwound, and Cisco stock came to symbolize the dotcom era's boom and bust.
